KW  - Monetary policy rules
KW  - Fiscal policy
KW  - Interest rate rules
KW  - Optimal policy
KW  - Nominal rigidities
AB  - We study in this article how the conduct of fiscal policy interacts with the choice of optimal monetary rules by a central bank. We consider a non-Ricardian model with nondistortionary fiscal policies, and compare two policy packages, one where fiscal and monetary policies are simultaneously optimized, and one where monetary policy is optimized under a given fiscal policy. We find a number of results that would not appear in the traditional Ricardian framework: (a) the optimal monetary rule may be activist when fiscal policy is kept inactive, whereas it is not when combined with optimal fiscal policy; (b) combining optimally fiscal and monetary policies may lead to far superior outcomes, even when, following Sargent and Wallace (1975, Journal of Political Economy 83, 241–254), government is allowed to react to much less information.
ER  - 

